CMunge <VERSION>
Copyright (c) 1999-2006 Robin Watts/Justin Fletcher

Make a RISC OS module header for a module written in C/C++.

Usage: cmunge [options] infile

Options:

  -h                 Output this information.
  -o <file>          Name the output AOF file.
  -s <file>          Name the output assembler file.
  -d <file>          Name a C header file that CMunge will generate.
  -xhdr <file>       Name a Assembler SWI header file that CMunge will
                     generate.
  -xh <file>         Name a C SWI header file that CMunge will generate.
  -p                 Pre-process the file with pre-processor before parsing.
  -px                Extended pre-processing of all content from
                     pre-processor.
  -I<directory>      Include <directory> on the #include search path.
  -D<symbol>=<value> 
  -D<symbol>         Define <symbol> on entry to the preprocessor.
  -U<symbol>         Undefine <symbol> on entry to the preprocessor.
  -depend <file>     Output 'make' include file dependency information to
                     <file>.
  -throwback         Use throwback for error processing.
  -zbase             Define symbol Image__RO_Base in generated header.
  -zerrors           Define errors and veneers only (for use in
                     applications).
  -zoslib            Use '#include "oslib/os.h"' (OSLib) instead of
                     '#include "kernel.h"' (Acorn) in generated C header
                     file.
  -zoslibpath        Use '#include "OSLib:Core/os.h"'.
  -blank             Generate a blank cmhg file to infile.
  -cmhg              Give warnings for non-CMHG values.
  -tgcc              Use GCC tool chain to generate output.
  -tlcc              Use LCC tool chain to generate output.
  -tnorcroft         Use Norcroft tool chain to generate output (default).
  -32bit             Generate 32-bit compatible code.
  -26bit             Generate 26-bit only code (default).
  -apcs 3/<flags>    Specify APCS variant to use.

APCS flags: (*=currently selected)
  /32[bit]           32 bit APCS variant
  /26[bit]          *26 bit APCS variant
  /reent[rant]       Reentrant APCS variant
  /nonreent[rant]   *Non reentrant APCS variant
  /fpe3              Floating point emulator 3 compatibility
  /fpe2             *Floating point emulator 2 compatibility
  /swst[ackcheck]   *Software stack checking APCS variant
  /noswst[ackcheck]  No software stack checking APCS variant
  /fpr[egargs]      *FP arguments passed in FP registers
  /nofpr[egargs]     FP arguments are not passed in FP registers
  /fp                Arguments referenced through the frame pointer
  /nofp             *Arguments referenced through the stack pointer
